   NDEP Home : Conduct Awareness Campaigns and Programs : Medicare
   Coverage for Blood Sugar Testing Campaign

   Medicare Coverage for Blood Sugar Testing
   Campaign NEW!



     Brochures for Patient Education

     Materials for Public Education Campaigns

   NDEP, in cooperation with the Health Care Financing Administration
   (HCFA), developed these materials to help explain Medicare's expanded
   coverage of diabetes supplies.

   Remember: All our publications are copyright-free. Please duplicate and
   distribute as many copies of these materials as desired.

Brochures for Patient Education [ top ]

   If you don't have access to a printer, you may order single copies for
   free. Limit 1 copy.
     * The power to control diabetes is in your hands (NDEP-38) [star.gif]
       This easy-to-read,12-page brochure provides information for
       Medicare beneficiaries who have diabetes. The brochure focuses on
       the importance of self-monitoring blood sugar levels and explains
       the Medicare benefits that help pay for diabetes equipment and
       supplies. Package of 25, $5. (pdf format)*
     * The power to control diabetes is in your hands, Photocopy Master
       (NDEP-38PM)
       Camera-ready modified version of NDEP-38.
     * El poder de controlar su diabetes esta en sus manos (NDEP-39)
       [star.gif]
       Spanish version of The power to control diabetes is in your hands
       brochure. Package of 25, $5. (pdf format)*
     * El poder de controlar su diabetes esta en sus manos, Original para
       Fotocopiar (NDEP-39PM)
       Camera-ready modified version of NDEP-39.

Materials for Public Education Campaigns [ top ]

   If you don't have access to a printer, you may order single copies for
   free.
     * The power to control diabetes is in your hands, Poster (NDEP-40)
       [star.gif]
       This striking 2-color poster conveys the importance of regular
       self-monitoring of blood sugar levels and explains Medicare
       coverage of diabetes testing equipment and supplies. Package of 25,
       $5. (pdf format)*
     * El poder de controlar su diabetes esta en sus manos, Afiche
       (NDEP-41) [star.gif]
       Spanish version of The power to control diabetes is in your hands
       poster. Package of 25, $5. (pdf format)*
     * The power to control diabetes is in your hands, Countertop Display
       (NDEP-42) [star.gif]
       This 2-color tabletop display conveys the importance of regular
       self-monitoring of blood sugar levels and Medicare coverage of
       diabetes testing equipment and supplies. Package of 10, $5. (pdf
       format)*
     * El poder de controlar su diabetes esta en sus manos, Exhibic√≠on de
       Contramesa (NDEP-43) [star.gif]
       Spanish version of The power to control diabetes is in your hands
       countertop display. Package of 10, $5. (pdf format)*


        [star.gif] Commercial printer-ready Zip cartridges available.
                            Call 1-800-860-8747.

   To order printed materials on how to control your diabetes, call the
   National Diabetes Education Program automated phone line at
   1-800-438-5383 or use the order form.

   Additional resources on financial assistance for diabetes are available
   from the National Diabetes Information Clearinghouse (NDIC).

   *This file is in PDF format, which requires the free Adobe Acrobat
   Reader for viewing.
   Attention visually impaired visitors: To use common screen reading
   programs with PDF documents, please visit access.adobe.com, which
   provides a set of free tools that convert PDF documents to simple HTML
   or ASCII text.
